  <description type="morphology">Leaves obovate to spatulate, apex broadly acute or occasionally rounded, short-awned, margins plane or rarely weakly recurved proximally, weakly bordered distally with 2–4 rows of slightly thicker-walled cells; costa excurrent, lacking an adaxial pad of cells, distally narrow, 2 cells across the convex or plane adaxial surface; distal laminal cells irregularly hexagonal, width 18–22(–27) µm wide, 1:1, smooth.  Sexual condition autoicous.  Sporophytes exerted.  Seta 0.25–0.4(–0.6) cm.  Capsule stegocarpic, not systylius, urceolate or obovate, erect and nearly straight, urn 0.6–1 mm; peristome absent; operculum 0.3–0.5 mm.  Spores 25–30 µm, spheric, densely papillose.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Capsules mature fall–spring.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Soil, calcareous soil with grasses, fields, lawns, roadsides;</description>
